First Lady Michelle Obama will host spouses of foreign leaders who are visiting the United States for the G-8 and NATO summits. She will invite them to the White House for a tour and lunch prepared by Chef José Andrés using produce from the White House Kitchen Garden. Mrs. Obama will then travel to Chicago and invite NATO leaders' spouses to visit the Gary Comer Youth Center, which supports youth on the South Side of Chicago. The Center offers various educational and extracurricular activities to help young people graduate from high school and pursue college and meaningful careers. The spouses will take a tour of the Center and attend performances by the South Shore Dance Drill Team, Muntu Dance Theater, and Soul Children of Chicago. They will also have a private lunch prepared by Chef Paul Kahan, followed by a private dinner at the Art Institute of Chicago.